    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paint formed of an emulsion of fatty and watery constituents. The standard emulsion is usually created with egg yolk and water, with variants of man-made emulsions created with whole egg, linseed oil, casein glue, gum, or wax.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
